<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 98-12-04 - Crankshaft/Flywheel Alignment Dowel Pin.</stitle>
    <tsi id="tSI981204" tsitype="engine">
        <tsinumber>98-12-04</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>March, 1998</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>Engines</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Crankshaft/Flywheel Alignment Dowel Pin.</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>T 444E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>A longer flywheel alignment dowel pin is now available. The length of the dowel pin was increased
                    from 25.4 mm (1.0 inch) to 44.45 mm (1.75 inch). This ensures proper crankshaft/flywheel alignment
                    during assembly.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="align" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>THE LONGER DOWEL IN WILL NOT WORK ON ENGINES WITH SERIAL NUMBER 505017 AND BELOW. THE LONGER
                        DOWEL PIN DOES NOT ALLOW THE OLD FLYWHEEL ADAPTER TO BUTT UP AGAINST THE NEW CRANKSHAFT.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">SERVICE PROCEDURE: REPLACEMENT CRANKSHAFT AND ENGINES WILL BE SUPPLIED WITH THE LONGER
                    DOWEL PIN.
                </emph>
                Before installing a new crankshaft a new crankshaft on engines with an old flywheel adapter, Serial
                Number 505017 and Below, remove the longer dowel pin, 44.45 mm (1.75 inch) in length, from the rear of
                the crankshaft and install the shorter dowel pin 25.5 mm (1.0 inch) in length into the rear of the
                crankshaft (refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f98120401">Proper Dowel Pin Selection
                    <xref refid="f98120401"/>
                </hotlnk>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="f98120401" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/EG8002.webp" type="webp" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Proper Dowel Pin Selection</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Parts Affected:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>New and revised parts are as follows, refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="te98120401">Parts List
                    <xref refid="te98120401"/>
                </hotlnk>
                :
            </para>
            <table id="te98120401" frame="all">
                <title>Table 1 Parts List</title>
                <tgroup cols="3" colsep="0" rowsep="1">
                    <colspec colwidth="1.2in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="2.0in"/>
                    <colspec colwidth="1.2in"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>New Number</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Description</para>
                            </entry>
